  "prompt": "What is the best programming languages in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, some of the most popular and in-demand programming languages were:\n\n1. JavaScript\n- Essential for web development\n- Versatile with frameworks like React and Angular\n- High demand in front-end and full-stack development\n\n2. Python\n- Growing popularity in data science\n- Machine learning and AI applications\n- Web development with Django and Flask\n- Simple and readable syntax\n\n3. Java\n- Enterprise software development\n- Android mobile app development\n- Widely used in large-scale systems\n- Strong job market\n\n4. C#\n- Microsoft/.NET ecosystem\n- Game development with Unity\n- Enterprise software\n- Windows application development\n\n5. Swift\n- iOS and macOS app development\n- Modern and safe language\n- Replacing Objective-C\n\n6. Go (Golang)\n- System programming\n- Cloud and network services\n- Developed by Google\n- Efficient performance\n\n7. Ruby\n- Web development with Ruby on Rails\n- Startup and tech community\n- Clean and readable syntax\n\n8. PHP\n- Web development\n- Content management systems\n- WordPress and server-side scripting\n\n9. TypeScript\n- Enhanced JavaScript\n- Better tooling and type safety\n- Supported by Microsoft\n\nEach language had strengths in different domains, and the \"best\" depended on specific project requirements.",
